olive oil
1 packet Beef Mince
1 packet Fine Breadcrumbs
1 sachet Kiwi Spice Blend
2 eggs
1 sachet Garlic & Herb Seasoning
1 packet chicken thigh
1 packet herbed pork sausages
1 packet Shredded Cheddar Cheese
1 Onion
3 courgette
2 packet Halloumi
4 Burger Bun
drizzle vinegar (balsamic or white wine)
1 tomato
1 bag Slaw Mix
1 packet mayonnaise
2 packet Mixed Salad Leaves
1 packet Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise

• Preheat BBQ to medium-high heat.
• In a medium bowl, combine beef mince, fine
breadcrumbs, kiwi spice blend and the eggs.
• Using damp hands, shape beef mixture into
4 evenly sized patties, slightly larger than your
burger buns.
• In a second medium bowl, combine garlic &
herb seasoning and a drizzle of olive oil. Add
chicken thighs and turn to coat.

• When BBQ is hot, grill herbed pork sausages,
turning occasionally, until cooked through and
slightly charred, 10-15 minutes.
• Meanwhile, grill chicken, turning occasionally,
until charred and cooked through, 8-12 minutes.
• Grill beef patties until just cooked through,
4-5 minutes each side.
• In the last 1-2 minutes of cook time, sprinkle
shredded Cheddar cheese over beef patties
and close the BBQ lid (or cover with foil) so the
cheese melts. Transfer everything to a serving
platter and cover to keep warm.
TIP: Chicken is cooked through when it's no longer
pink inside.

• Thinly slice onion. Thinly slice courgette into
ribbons lengthways. Cut halloumi into 1cm thick
slices. Slice burger buns in half.
• In a small bowl, combine onion and a drizzle of
olive oil.
• In a large bowl, combine courgette, a drizzle of
olive oil and a pinch of salt and pepper.
• Grill courgette until charred and tender,
3-5 minutes each side. Transfer to a serving
bowl. Add a drizzle of vinegar, tossing to
combine. Cover to keep warm and set aside.
• Grill onions on a flat plate, until tender,
4-5 minutes. Transfer to a serving bowl. Cover
and set aside.

• Add halloumi to BBQ flat plate and grill until
golden brown, 1-2 minutes each side.
• Meanwhile, grill burger buns, cut-side down,
until lightly golden, 1-2 minutes.
• When done, transfer halloumi and buns to
serving plates.
TIP: Avoid using the grill plate to cook your haloumi
in case it gets stuck!

• Thinly slice tomato.
• In a third medium bowl, combine slaw mix and
mayonnaise.
• In a fourth medium bowl, combine mixed salad
leaves and a drizzle of vinegar and olive oil.
Season to taste.

• Slice grilled chicken.
• Spread burger buns with some dill & parsley
mayonnaise. Top with a beef patty, tomato
and dressed salad leaves. Transfer remaining
dill & parsley mayonnaise to a small bowl.
• Bring everything to the table to serve. Enjoy!
TIP: Customise your burger by using slaw or adding
halloumi!